"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-28-2024-olympic-qualifier-its-do-or-die-vs-super-falcons-south-africa-coach-ellis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Banyana Banyana of South Africa head coach Desiree Ellis says her side's 2024 Olympic Games final qualifying round fixture against the Super Falcons of Nigeria will be a \\\"do or die\\\" affair.  The reigning African champions booked a date with old foes Nigeria after a 1-0 victory against Tanzania on Tuesday night.  Former African women's Player of the Year, Thembi Kgatlana scored the winning goal in the second half.  South Africa won the tie 4-0 on aggregate.  \\\"It will be do or die (vs Nigeria),\\\" Ellis declared after the game against Tanzania.  \\\"We want to have an early camp, we will improve our chances when we prepare early and very well.\\\"  South Africa and Nigeria will clash in a two-legged match between April 1-9, 2024.  The overall winners will be one of Africa's representatives at the 2024 Paris Olympics.  FA Cup: All you need to know about quarter-final draw  Enyimba defender Alalibo seeks positive result against Gombe United  UCL: South Africa's Bartlett blames Galatasaray's 4-0 defeat to Liverpool on Osimhen's injury  South Africa: Ndah still awaiting work permit to debut for Stellenbosch FC  Nigeria, South Africa strengthen military ties to tackle terrorism, modern threats  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"